5|$|Biofuels have {{a limited}} ability to replace <b>fossil</b> <b>fuels</b> {{and should not be}} {{regarded}} as a ‘silver bullet’ to deal with transport emissions. However, they offer the prospect of increased market competition and oil price moderation. A healthy supply of alternative energy sources will help to combat gasoline price spikes and reduce dependency on <b>fossil</b> <b>fuels,</b> especially in the transport sector. Using transportation fuels more efficiently is also an integral part of a sustainable transport strategy.|$|E
